{"questionId":"9076400","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>To determine the acceleration due to gravity, a small metal sphere is dropped from rest and&nbsp;the time it takes to fall through a known distance and open a trapdoor is measured.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4747/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_15.43.42.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/01\"></p>\n<p>The following data are available.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {{\\text{Diameter of metal sphere}}}&amp;{ = 12.0 \\pm 0.1{\\text{ mm}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Distance between the point of release and the trapdoor}}}&amp;{ = 654 \\pm 2{\\text{ mm}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Measured time for fall}}}&amp;{ = 0.363 \\pm 0.002{\\text{ s}}} \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable columnalign=\"left\" rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Diameter of metal sphere</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>12.0</mn>\n          <mo>±</mo>\n          <mn>0.1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mm</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Distance between the point of release and the trapdoor</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>654</mn>\n          <mo>±</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mm</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Measured time for fall</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>0.363</mn>\n          <mo>±</mo>\n          <mn>0.002</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;s</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the distance fallen, in m, by the centre of mass of the sphere including an&nbsp;estimate of the absolute uncertainty in your answer.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>distance fallen = 654 – 12 = 642 <strong>«</strong>mm<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>absolute uncertainty<strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong>= 2&nbsp;+&nbsp;0.1 <strong>«</strong>mm<strong>»</strong> ≈ 2 × 10<sup>–3</sup> <strong>«</strong>m<strong>»&nbsp;or</strong>&nbsp;= 2.1&nbsp;× 10<sup>–3</sup> <strong>«</strong>m<strong>»&nbsp;or</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>2.0&nbsp;× 10<sup>–3</sup> <strong>«</strong>m<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept answers in mm or m</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong><em>&nbsp;</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076400","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the distance fallen, in m, by the centre of mass of the sphere including an estimate of the absolute uncertainty in your answer.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}